**BCC (Blind Carbon Copy):**

When you include someone's email address in the "bcc" field, it means that you are sending a copy of the email to that person, but their email address will not be visible to the other recipients of the email.

In summary, the main difference between "cc" and "bcc" is that the email addresses of people who are included in the "cc" field will be visible to all the other recipients of the email, whereas the email addresses of people who are included in the "bcc" field will not be visible to any of the other recipients of the email.
